1
00:00:06,930 --> 00:00:11,970
Marry me, Ji Hyeok.

2
00:00:15,790 --> 00:00:17,700
What?

3
00:00:17,700 --> 00:00:20,500
I'm asking you to marry me.

4
00:00:20,500 --> 00:00:21,980
Why are you doing this?

5
00:00:21,980 --> 00:00:23,720
Do you think I don't know that

6
00:00:23,720 --> 00:00:27,820
you've openly declared that
you're anti-marriage and

7
00:00:27,820 --> 00:00:30,630
still asking you to marry me?

8
00:00:30,630 --> 00:00:32,680
I don't want to respond because this is so absurd.

9
00:00:32,680 --> 00:00:34,410
Stop talking nonsense and

10
00:00:34,410 --> 00:00:37,300
finish your thought if you have something to say.

11
00:00:37,300 --> 00:00:39,700
I'll listen and show reactions.

12
00:00:43,080 --> 00:00:45,330
You know I've been in love.

13
00:00:45,330 --> 00:00:47,760
A dead serious one.

14
00:00:48,440 --> 00:00:51,770
I said I'll never forget him. No...

15
00:00:51,770 --> 00:00:54,610
I decided I'd be with him until I die.

16
00:00:54,610 --> 00:00:57,920
That's how much I loved him.

17
00:00:59,270 --> 00:01:03,450
I'd run to him now if only I knew where he was.

18
00:01:03,450 --> 00:01:06,790
That's how much lingering feelings
I had for that relationship.

19
00:01:08,270 --> 00:01:10,880
But you don't end up together just
because you're in love.

20
00:01:10,880 --> 00:01:13,000
As you already know.

21
00:01:15,180 --> 00:01:20,590
I need to give up since he's gone,

22
00:01:20,590 --> 00:01:23,690
but I can't give up on the
privilege my dad gives me.

23
00:01:25,120 --> 00:01:27,060
I think you are anti-marriage

24
00:01:27,060 --> 00:01:30,100
because you'd lose more than you gain

25
00:01:30,100 --> 00:01:32,050
through a marriage.

26
00:01:32,050 --> 00:01:33,240
Are you done?

27
00:01:33,240 --> 00:01:35,770
I agree with you.

28
00:01:35,770 --> 00:01:39,420
I've learned that love doesn't lead to marriage.

29
00:01:39,420 --> 00:01:42,560
That's why I'm making a suggestion.

30
00:01:42,560 --> 00:01:46,990
Why shouldn't you marry if you earn a lot from it?

31
00:01:46,990 --> 00:01:49,540
I'm not suggesting we become
a perfect, lovely couple.

32
00:01:49,540 --> 00:01:50,760
But still…

33
00:01:50,760 --> 00:01:54,240
Are you anti-marriage because you
thought you'd never meet your love?

34
00:01:54,240 --> 00:01:55,340
That's not it.

35
00:01:55,340 --> 00:01:59,790
Why shouldn't you have a loveless marriage, then?

36
00:01:59,790 --> 00:02:04,540
Not only that, you'll never love anyone.

37
00:02:04,540 --> 00:02:07,530
You said you can control your emotions.

38
00:02:12,280 --> 00:02:14,750
What would I gain

39
00:02:14,750 --> 00:02:17,730
by marrying you right now?

40
00:02:19,230 --> 00:02:21,750
Should I start negotiating or something?

41
00:02:21,750 --> 00:02:24,160
I'm the only daughter of Haneul Construction.

42
00:02:24,160 --> 00:02:26,120
My father, CEO Jeong Ho Yeong

43
00:02:26,120 --> 00:02:30,530
believes that a woman should never run the company.

44
00:02:31,340 --> 00:02:33,060
You know that already.

45
00:02:33,060 --> 00:02:35,840
There was a rumor like that going around.

46
00:02:35,840 --> 00:02:38,440
And you never know.

47
00:02:38,440 --> 00:02:42,490
If we grow attached to each other, we'll agree

48
00:02:42,490 --> 00:02:44,720
to become a real couple.

49
00:02:44,720 --> 00:02:46,900
Or...

50
00:02:46,900 --> 00:02:50,960
we'll get divorced after my dad passes away.

51
00:02:50,960 --> 00:02:54,690
Well, although I don't know when.

52
00:02:56,570 --> 00:02:58,960
Aren't you laying your cards too much?

53
00:02:58,960 --> 00:03:01,780
You understand that I'm not joking.

54
00:03:01,780 --> 00:03:04,050
Give it a thought, then.

55
00:03:04,050 --> 00:03:07,310
See you back here next week.

56
00:03:23,710 --> 00:03:25,260
 

57
00:03:26,490 --> 00:03:28,780
What a strange world.

58
00:03:40,710 --> 00:03:41,860
Yes, Father.

59
00:03:41,860 --> 00:03:43,140
 Yes, Ji Hyeok. 

60
00:03:43,140 --> 00:03:46,270
 Do you have a plan after work today? 

61
00:03:47,220 --> 00:03:49,850
 Did you know? 

62
00:03:51,120 --> 00:03:53,090
No, I have no plans.

63
00:03:53,090 --> 00:03:55,910
 Let's meet outside after you're off work. 

64
00:03:55,910 --> 00:03:57,790
Where should I meet you?

65
00:03:57,790 --> 00:04:00,250
How about Yeong Bo's shop?

66
00:04:01,400 --> 00:04:03,570
- Hey.
- Let me do it.

67
00:04:03,570 --> 00:04:05,130
Don't take this fun away from me.

68
00:04:05,130 --> 00:04:08,310
I haven't drunk with someone in a while.

69
00:04:08,310 --> 00:04:09,810
You're right.

70
00:04:11,270 --> 00:04:12,530
Here.

71
00:04:13,500 --> 00:04:15,950
Wow, I'm jealous.

72
00:04:15,950 --> 00:04:19,140
Having a son to drink with.

73
00:04:22,010 --> 00:04:24,460
Mr. Choi has late-stage cancer.

74
00:04:24,460 --> 00:04:26,630
That's why that happened.

75
00:04:28,210 --> 00:04:29,910
Oh, I see.

76
00:04:29,910 --> 00:04:31,400
His son is young.

77
00:04:31,400 --> 00:04:34,190
That's why he thinks differently from his father.

78
00:04:34,190 --> 00:04:38,480
But he was acting cocky, so I chewed him out.

79
00:04:39,920 --> 00:04:40,970
Yes.

80
00:04:40,970 --> 00:04:44,040
I've been meeting with people in the industry.

81
00:04:44,040 --> 00:04:45,980
I'll get a job soon.

82
00:04:45,980 --> 00:04:50,240
I was going to explain the situation later.

83
00:04:50,240 --> 00:04:51,480
Okay.

84
00:04:51,480 --> 00:04:54,900
Do Ji Wan and Su Bin know?

85
00:04:54,900 --> 00:04:56,410
Not yet.

86
00:04:56,410 --> 00:04:58,570
But you should tell them as soon as possible.

87
00:04:58,570 --> 00:05:00,590
No, I'll get a job first.

88
00:05:00,590 --> 00:05:04,280
There's no need to disappoint the kids.

89
00:05:04,280 --> 00:05:06,940
Because you don't know when that will be.

90
00:05:06,940 --> 00:05:08,200
What?

91
00:05:08,200 --> 00:05:11,710
It's not easy to get a job after you retire.

92
00:05:11,710 --> 00:05:14,010
Be prepared for that.

93
00:05:14,010 --> 00:05:17,530
That's how it is after you retire.

94
00:05:17,530 --> 00:05:19,330
It's just reality.

95
00:05:19,330 --> 00:05:21,020
Yes.

96
00:05:21,020 --> 00:05:24,300
It's not easy. It must be hard.

97
00:05:24,300 --> 00:05:26,780
But it's not like I don't know that.

98
00:05:26,780 --> 00:05:29,260
I have friends who retired before I did

99
00:05:29,260 --> 00:05:34,120
and a ton of them work outside
when it's freezing cold.

100
00:05:34,120 --> 00:05:38,690
But still, I got recruited even before I retired.

101
00:05:38,690 --> 00:05:42,360
There has to be a reason why.

102
00:05:42,360 --> 00:05:44,800
I'll let the kids know.

103
00:05:44,800 --> 00:05:47,480
It must be hard for Mom and
Grandma to pretend, too.

104
00:05:47,480 --> 00:05:49,630
Don't act like you know.

105
00:05:49,630 --> 00:05:51,810
Don't tell Ji Wan and Su Bin.

106
00:05:51,810 --> 00:05:53,920
Don't let Mom and Grandma know, either.

107
00:05:53,920 --> 00:05:55,940
It shouldn't be a secret, Father.

108
00:05:55,940 --> 00:05:58,220
A lot of people go through this.

109
00:05:58,220 --> 00:06:00,590
 We can only leap so far. 

110
00:06:00,590 --> 00:06:05,700
Don't assume your father will end up the same way.

111
00:06:05,700 --> 00:06:08,900
We're not in a position to worry
about living expenses.

112
00:06:08,900 --> 00:06:10,620
You have a good job.

113
00:06:10,620 --> 00:06:12,400
Ji Wan doesn't ask for money.

114
00:06:12,400 --> 00:06:15,110
We just need to help Su Bin.
What's there to worry about?

115
00:06:15,110 --> 00:06:18,300
It'll only take two or three months.

116
00:06:24,500 --> 00:06:26,730
What kind of work are you thinking of?

117
00:06:26,730 --> 00:06:28,470
Textiles. What else?

118
00:06:28,470 --> 00:06:31,190
Don't just look at textiles. Broaden your search.

119
00:06:31,190 --> 00:06:32,710
You little.

120
00:06:32,710 --> 00:06:35,070
I can manage that myself.

121
00:06:36,070 --> 00:06:37,410
Where do you spend time outside?

122
00:06:37,410 --> 00:06:38,880
What do you mean by where?

123
00:06:38,880 --> 00:06:42,500
I'm busy meeting people in the
industry to look for a job.

124
00:06:42,500 --> 00:06:46,120
I go hiking and play pool sometimes, too.

125
00:06:46,120 --> 00:06:48,850
I meet my college buddies, too.

126
00:06:51,410 --> 00:06:52,910
Okay.

127
00:06:56,500 --> 00:07:01,570
Aigoo. How long has it been
since I walked with you like this?

128
00:07:01,570 --> 00:07:03,830
It's been a long time.

129
00:07:05,710 --> 00:07:07,150
Hey,

130
00:07:07,150 --> 00:07:10,820
why am I looking up at you like this?

131
00:07:10,820 --> 00:07:14,420
I looked down at you like this just yesterday.

132
00:07:14,420 --> 00:07:16,980
That was ages ago.

133
00:07:16,980 --> 00:07:20,920
I've been taller than you for a million years.

134
00:07:20,920 --> 00:07:22,560
Is that so?

135
00:07:24,550 --> 00:07:27,290
You're tall. Yes.

136
00:07:27,290 --> 00:07:30,070
Of course. I'm your son.

137
00:07:33,410 --> 00:07:35,290
 Let me leave now. 

138
00:07:35,290 --> 00:07:37,400
 I need to run a bit. 

139
00:07:46,040 --> 00:07:48,220
 If you can't hide your discomfort, 

140
00:07:48,220 --> 00:07:51,360
 quit your job as a manager at our cafe. 

141
00:08:07,750 --> 00:08:09,390
 All right, Lee Ji Hyeok. 

142
00:08:09,390 --> 00:08:11,050
 I'll forget everything. 

143
00:08:11,050 --> 00:08:14,300
 I'll move on completely. 

144
00:08:19,640 --> 00:08:21,330
 I've already thought about this. 

145
00:08:21,330 --> 00:08:23,390
 You think I haven't? 

146
00:08:23,390 --> 00:08:25,670
 Why am I incompatible with you? 

147
00:08:25,670 --> 00:08:27,350
 Because I'm not feminine? 

148
00:08:27,350 --> 00:08:29,080
 Because I don't adorn myself? 

149
00:08:29,080 --> 00:08:31,730
 Because I have too strong a personality? 

150
00:08:31,730 --> 00:08:33,830
 Because we have different tastes? 

151
00:08:33,830 --> 00:08:35,950
 It was none of those. 

152
00:08:35,950 --> 00:08:40,120
 The only thing would be our backgrounds. 

153
00:08:40,120 --> 00:08:42,910
 Because my family is poor? 

154
00:08:42,910 --> 00:08:45,710
 Because I don't make enough money? 

155
00:08:46,590 --> 00:08:48,110
 It's definitely not that. 

156
00:08:48,110 --> 00:08:50,360
 Because you're anti-marriage. 

157
00:08:50,360 --> 00:08:54,640
 You wouldn't care about that
since you won't marry. 

158
00:08:55,690 --> 00:08:57,960
 What is it, then? 

159
00:08:57,960 --> 00:09:00,900
 I don't know why you won't tell me, but... 

160
00:09:06,930 --> 00:09:08,650
 

161
00:09:10,590 --> 00:09:12,430
No.

162
00:09:12,430 --> 00:09:14,980
I won't console myself with alcohol.

163
00:09:14,980 --> 00:09:17,250
I can overcome this alone.

164
00:10:37,640 --> 00:10:41,300
There's leftover ginseng wine
from the memorial service.

165
00:10:57,870 --> 00:11:01,510
I saw Kang Oh making a highball with it.

166
00:11:23,540 --> 00:11:26,310
Gosh, seriously...

167
00:11:26,310 --> 00:11:28,030
My head hurts.

168
00:11:29,540 --> 00:11:31,400
I'm dying. Seriously.

169
00:11:31,400 --> 00:11:36,300
- Isn't that your sister?
- I think so.

170
00:11:36,300 --> 00:11:38,190
Gosh, ouch!

171
00:11:38,190 --> 00:11:40,110
Eun Oh.

172
00:11:44,060 --> 00:11:45,340
- Eun Oh!
- Ji Eun Oh!

173
00:11:45,340 --> 00:11:48,650
My goodness. Eun Oh!

174
00:11:49,840 --> 00:11:51,400
 By the way, Da Jeong... 

175
00:11:51,400 --> 00:11:55,520
when people say, "Elders are welcome,"

176
00:11:55,520 --> 00:11:58,230
how old do they expect you to be?

177
00:11:58,230 --> 00:12:00,240
Who welcomes elders?

178
00:12:00,240 --> 00:12:04,310
Well, I saw it at a restaurant or something.

179
00:12:04,310 --> 00:12:07,680
They said that in a job poster.

180
00:12:07,680 --> 00:12:10,200
Probably 65, then.

181
00:12:10,200 --> 00:12:13,410
The subway is free starting at that age.

182
00:12:14,730 --> 00:12:17,280
Sixty-five?

183
00:12:19,260 --> 00:12:21,680
That's a baby's age compared to you.

184
00:12:21,680 --> 00:12:23,770
Sixty-five definitely is.

185
00:13:02,400 --> 00:13:06,800
How hungover is she that
you even brought in Hye Na?

186
00:13:06,800 --> 00:13:10,170
She was in a hospital all night.

187
00:13:10,170 --> 00:13:12,110
Not knowing she mixed alcohol,

188
00:13:12,110 --> 00:13:14,520
they thought she took poison
since she was passed out.

189
00:13:14,520 --> 00:13:16,810
They even pumped her stomach.

190
00:13:19,250 --> 00:13:21,520
With exhaustion and the flu,

191
00:13:21,520 --> 00:13:24,250
she needs to rest for about a week.

192
00:13:39,860 --> 00:13:43,090
 Ji Hyeok, I think Eun Oh is very sick. 

193
00:13:43,090 --> 00:13:45,580
 She was sent to the hospital. 

194
00:13:57,950 --> 00:13:59,000
 

195
00:14:03,580 --> 00:14:05,104
So?

196
00:14:05,104 --> 00:14:06,120
What?

197
00:14:06,120 --> 00:14:08,080
I saw your text about Eun Oh.

198
00:14:08,080 --> 00:14:09,970
How is she now?

199
00:14:09,970 --> 00:14:12,170
She's resting at home now.

200
00:14:14,410 --> 00:14:16,300
That's good, then.

201
00:14:16,300 --> 00:14:19,000
- I'll hang up.
 - Hey. 

202
00:14:30,750 --> 00:14:32,140
 Yes, Director. 

203
00:14:32,140 --> 00:14:34,890
Please call Yurim Traditional Clinic.

204
00:15:00,430 --> 00:15:01,900
 

205
00:15:10,530 --> 00:15:11,990
Goodness.

206
00:15:11,990 --> 00:15:14,250
Eun Oh...

207
00:15:14,250 --> 00:15:17,600
someone sent you expensive traditional medicine.

208
00:15:17,600 --> 00:15:20,450
My gosh. There's fruit and tea, too.

209
00:15:20,450 --> 00:15:24,050
It's filled with snacks, too.

210
00:15:26,300 --> 00:15:28,510
Park Seong Jae.

211
00:15:28,510 --> 00:15:30,400
Who's this?

212
00:15:32,300 --> 00:15:34,660
 I hope you feel better soon. 

213
00:15:34,660 --> 00:15:36,690
He's a regular.

214
00:15:38,180 --> 00:15:39,770
You sure are lucky with food.

215
00:15:39,770 --> 00:15:41,450
A new bakery sent you bread, too.

216
00:15:41,450 --> 00:15:44,060
How did they know you love bread?

217
00:15:44,060 --> 00:15:45,350
You eat it.

218
00:15:45,350 --> 00:15:46,730
Really? Thank you.

219
00:15:46,730 --> 00:15:48,330
Gosh, stop.

220
00:15:48,330 --> 00:15:50,640
Eat whatever she doesn't want.

221
00:15:50,640 --> 00:15:54,070
Eun Oh, since you had porridge,

222
00:15:54,070 --> 00:15:57,020
pick a bread you want and have some

223
00:15:57,020 --> 00:15:59,630
when you have an appetite.

224
00:15:59,630 --> 00:16:01,240
Get up.

225
00:16:05,580 --> 00:16:07,410
Pick one.

226
00:16:11,750 --> 00:16:14,140
My goodness.

227
00:16:15,270 --> 00:16:18,800
It's yeontanbbang and agungbbang.

228
00:16:18,800 --> 00:16:22,630
They mean serious business these days.
They promote like crazy.

229
00:16:22,630 --> 00:16:27,260
"I hope the deep scent of sweetness comforts you."

230
00:16:27,260 --> 00:16:29,390
I got the chills.

231
00:16:34,930 --> 00:16:36,640
Take them.

232
00:16:57,500 --> 00:17:02,000
Mr. Lee, my knees hurt too much.

233
00:17:02,000 --> 00:17:05,760
Well, your feet are pointing forward.

234
00:17:05,760 --> 00:17:08,430
Make them point off to the side more.

235
00:17:08,430 --> 00:17:10,750
The width should be shoulder width

236
00:17:10,750 --> 00:17:12,270
and you go down like that.

237
00:17:12,270 --> 00:17:15,730
When you squat, try to fold the hip joints.

238
00:17:15,730 --> 00:17:20,220
Get up by using the glutes and thigh muscles.

239
00:17:20,220 --> 00:17:21,910
Which part is the glutes?

240
00:17:21,910 --> 00:17:24,370
Well, the glutes are...

241
00:17:24,370 --> 00:17:26,090
Right here?

242
00:17:28,870 --> 00:17:30,190
What?

243
00:17:37,050 --> 00:17:39,020
What are you doing?

244
00:17:51,450 --> 00:17:53,150
I'm sorry, Director.

245
00:17:53,150 --> 00:17:54,850
Hey.

246
00:17:54,850 --> 00:17:57,110
Your girlfriend wasn't even watching,
but to be loyal to her,

247
00:17:57,110 --> 00:17:58,960
you refused to have female clients.

248
00:17:58,960 --> 00:18:01,380
And you refuse to lay a finger on them.

249
00:18:01,380 --> 00:18:02,950
How will you be a personal trainer?

250
00:18:02,950 --> 00:18:07,020
It's not because of my girlfriend.
It's just me, sir.

251
00:18:07,020 --> 00:18:08,400
So, pack your stuff.

252
00:18:08,400 --> 00:18:10,570
I have my clients. How could I-

253
00:18:10,570 --> 00:18:13,390
Call the Labor Department if you think it's unfair.

254
00:18:17,990 --> 00:18:21,370
Never mind. I'll pack my stuff.

255
00:18:33,600 --> 00:18:36,760
Why did I buy you?

256
00:18:52,330 --> 00:18:56,150
 ♫ It's okay not to tell me ♫ 

257
00:18:56,150 --> 00:19:02,600
 ♫ Lean on me and close your eyes ♫ 

258
00:19:02,600 --> 00:19:07,100
 ♫ And you'll feel better ♫ 

259
00:19:07,100 --> 00:19:10,910
 ♫ It's okay to rest sometimes ♫ 

260
00:19:10,910 --> 00:19:15,970
 ♫ You've been working hard ♫ 

261
00:19:15,970 --> 00:19:19,210
 ♫ It's okay to pause for a moment ♫ 

262
00:19:19,210 --> 00:19:20,990
 

263
00:19:20,990 --> 00:19:25,180
 ♫ A tiring day has passed ♫ 

264
00:19:25,180 --> 00:19:29,200
 ♫ Yet in the same spot ♫ 

265
00:19:30,850 --> 00:19:32,800
 The customer can't answer the call right now. 

266
00:19:32,800 --> 00:19:40,950
 ♫ Just saying, "Thank you for your hard work" ♫ 

267
00:20:00,190 --> 00:20:02,100
 I want to be alone for a while. 

268
00:20:02,100 --> 00:20:03,880
 I'll be in touch. 

269
00:20:14,070 --> 00:20:17,710
What do you think? This is
a refreshing early summer look.

270
00:20:17,710 --> 00:20:20,930
Sleeveless shirts are only for mid-summer?

271
00:20:20,930 --> 00:20:22,600
No, no.

272
00:20:25,160 --> 00:20:27,360
