00:39:09,410 --> 00:39:13,490
I'm better than before because I rested plenty.

547
00:39:14,510 --> 00:39:16,410
Where are you coming from?

548
00:39:16,410 --> 00:39:18,170
The cafe I built opened.

549
00:39:18,170 --> 00:39:22,050
I stopped by to deliver an opening
gift and check for flaws.

550
00:39:22,050 --> 00:39:23,970
Do you have a new project?

551
00:39:23,970 --> 00:39:25,520
Not yet.

552
00:39:35,370 --> 00:39:38,560
Right. The students sent me an email.

553
00:39:38,560 --> 00:39:41,070
For the 30th anniversary,

554
00:39:41,070 --> 00:39:43,440
they came up with 30 items.

555
00:39:43,440 --> 00:39:46,430
Don't they have classes and exams?

556
00:39:46,430 --> 00:39:50,030
Will they only attend club events all semester?

557
00:39:50,030 --> 00:39:52,870
Why are they so obsessed with the club?

558
00:39:52,870 --> 00:39:54,980
You were like that in college, too.

559
00:39:54,980 --> 00:40:00,380
It's because I was going
to switch to interior design.

560
00:40:00,380 --> 00:40:01,930
They want to work on two houses this time.

561
00:40:01,930 --> 00:40:04,340
During the entire summer vacation.

562
00:40:04,340 --> 00:40:06,600
I can make a plan for them,

563
00:40:06,600 --> 00:40:10,370
but they'll have to beg the sunbaes
in technical fields, right?

564
00:40:12,080 --> 00:40:13,540
Eun Oh.

565
00:40:20,650 --> 00:40:22,290
Don't try too hard.

566
00:40:23,030 --> 00:40:24,160
What?

567
00:40:24,160 --> 00:40:28,240
You don't have to try so hard to talk.

568
00:40:29,520 --> 00:40:33,700
I've always been chatty going somewhere with you.

569
00:40:33,700 --> 00:40:35,720
Not this much.

570
00:40:35,720 --> 00:40:37,470
You used to catch a breath.

571
00:40:38,300 --> 00:40:40,570
D-Did I?

572
00:40:40,570 --> 00:40:44,400
But you're really annoying sometimes.

573
00:40:44,400 --> 00:40:46,580
You're too honest.

574
00:40:46,580 --> 00:40:48,380
Not always.

575
00:40:49,410 --> 00:40:52,320
I'm usually honest,

576
00:40:52,320 --> 00:40:56,470
but sometimes I pretend to be. Pretty often.

577
00:40:57,840 --> 00:41:00,980
When do you pretend to be honest?

578
00:41:01,790 --> 00:41:05,040
When I need to, when I feel uncomfortable,

579
00:41:06,460 --> 00:41:08,230
and when I feel gutless?

580
00:41:09,420 --> 00:41:12,500
I guess you can't help it, either.

581
00:41:14,030 --> 00:41:16,320
Everyone is like that.

582
00:41:16,320 --> 00:41:20,290
You think anyone's special? You fool.

583
00:41:34,680 --> 00:41:36,140
Go inside.

584
00:41:37,280 --> 00:41:40,100
I thought you were going to the cafe.

585
00:41:40,100 --> 00:41:42,140
Seong Jae told me that you returned to work.

586
00:41:42,140 --> 00:41:44,100
So, I stopped by briefly.

587
00:41:49,230 --> 00:41:51,520
When you date from now on,

588
00:41:52,580 --> 00:41:55,490
meet someone nice, not someone you like.

589
00:41:56,520 --> 00:41:58,390
Liking someone is based on feelings.

590
00:41:58,390 --> 00:42:00,110
Those feelings...

591
00:42:02,300 --> 00:42:04,230
don't have much power.

592
00:42:11,740 --> 00:42:15,360
That was pretty cool advice.

593
00:42:17,570 --> 00:42:20,740
Eat well. You look thin.

594
00:42:22,690 --> 00:42:24,060
Okay.

595
00:42:24,840 --> 00:42:27,440
Take care, Sunbae.

596
00:42:30,200 --> 00:42:42,220
 ♫ I take a step forward slowly,
hoping to reach you ♫ 

597
00:43:09,340 --> 00:43:11,200
Would you like to order?

598
00:43:11,200 --> 00:43:15,180
Actually, are you the designer of this portfolio?

599
00:43:15,180 --> 00:43:17,150
Well, no. It's not mine.

600
00:43:17,150 --> 00:43:20,130
There she is. It's hers.

601
00:43:23,890 --> 00:43:26,050
By chance...

602
00:43:26,050 --> 00:43:29,770
Hello. Are you feeling better?

603
00:43:29,770 --> 00:43:32,090
It's you, the lady from the subway.

604
00:43:32,090 --> 00:43:34,240
Yes, thanks to you.

605
00:43:34,240 --> 00:43:35,520
That's a relief.

606
00:43:35,520 --> 00:43:37,840
Eun Oh, do you know her?

607
00:43:37,840 --> 00:43:40,360
- Well-
- I was curious about the designer of this.

608
00:43:40,360 --> 00:43:41,960
It was you.

609
00:43:41,960 --> 00:43:44,130
Well, yes.

610
00:43:44,130 --> 00:43:49,220
Could we talk briefly right now?

611
00:43:51,030 --> 00:43:53,030
We happen to be slow right now.

612
00:43:53,030 --> 00:43:55,750
A moment would be okay.

613
00:44:07,170 --> 00:44:09,430
You had company.

614
00:44:09,430 --> 00:44:11,340
We're done talking.

615
00:44:16,200 --> 00:44:19,030
 I accepted it and gave up. 

616
00:44:19,030 --> 00:44:20,930
 I'll try my best. 

617
00:44:20,930 --> 00:44:23,590
 Because we have to go back to the way we were. 

618
00:44:24,460 --> 00:44:26,470
 If you like her so much, 

619
00:44:26,470 --> 00:44:29,540
 why did you let her ask me out and get hurt? 

620
00:44:29,540 --> 00:44:31,590
 Whenever I approached her, 

621
00:44:31,590 --> 00:44:34,180
 you told me to quit. 

622
00:44:34,180 --> 00:44:36,310
 You aren't interested. 

623
00:44:36,310 --> 00:44:38,800
That I'm not qualified.

624
00:44:38,800 --> 00:44:41,070
That I probably...

625
00:44:41,070 --> 00:44:43,530
don't have the right.

626
00:44:45,680 --> 00:44:47,440
You don't have to come in, Ms. Kim.

627
00:44:47,440 --> 00:44:49,200
We don't need tea, either.

628
00:44:49,200 --> 00:44:51,260
This is a surprise inspection.

629
00:44:52,000 --> 00:44:56,040
I heard you often leave for 30 minutes to an hour.

630
00:44:58,640 --> 00:45:01,190
This is inappropriate for you as my boss

631
00:45:01,190 --> 00:45:02,830
and even as my father.

632
00:45:02,830 --> 00:45:05,460
I have both reasons.

633
00:45:05,460 --> 00:45:08,840
"I want to marry someone I meet naturally.

634
00:45:08,840 --> 00:45:11,020
If I do marry."

635
00:45:11,020 --> 00:45:12,800
That was vague.

636
00:45:12,800 --> 00:45:16,960
Make it clear if you intend to marry or not.

637
00:45:16,960 --> 00:45:19,790
Are you relaxed because the sales went up?

638
00:45:21,200 --> 00:45:25,410
Did you put me in this position
without giving me any time?

639
00:45:25,410 --> 00:45:28,830
I told you how I feel about marriage.

640
00:45:28,830 --> 00:45:30,560
I'll give you until the end of the year.

641
00:45:30,560 --> 00:45:32,600
If you can't find someone until then,

642
00:45:32,600 --> 00:45:35,240
that means you lack ability.

643
00:45:35,240 --> 00:45:39,660
Marry the person I set you up with then.

644
00:45:50,750 --> 00:45:53,620
There's a project I'm working on.

645
00:45:53,620 --> 00:45:57,070
I was looking for an interior designer.

646
00:45:57,070 --> 00:45:58,650
But I happened to...

647
00:45:58,650 --> 00:46:01,650
Right. What's your name?

648
00:46:02,540 --> 00:46:04,920
I'm Ji Eun Oh.

649
00:46:06,280 --> 00:46:10,510
That's why your company name was Eunoh-ism Design.

650
00:46:10,510 --> 00:46:12,000
Yes.

651
00:46:15,810 --> 00:46:18,140
I'm Ko Seong Hui.

652
00:46:19,030 --> 00:46:21,580
Should I say an art and design space?

653
00:46:21,580 --> 00:46:24,150
I was planning for a space like that.

654
00:46:24,150 --> 00:46:26,610
I just happened to see your portfolio.

655
00:46:26,610 --> 00:46:28,760
It grabbed my attention immediately.

656
00:46:29,550 --> 00:46:32,320
Oh, I see.

657
00:46:32,320 --> 00:46:34,320
I'd like to hire you.

658
00:46:34,320 --> 00:46:36,760
But you don't seem to have a lot of experience.

659
00:46:36,760 --> 00:46:41,270
No. I started interior design a year ago.

660
00:46:41,270 --> 00:46:44,750
Three commercial buildings,
and this cafe. Four projects?

661
00:46:44,750 --> 00:46:47,760
Yes. I designed a few hoobaes' studio apartments,

662
00:46:47,760 --> 00:46:51,260
but those were more for my experience.

663
00:46:52,460 --> 00:46:56,530
I'm not sure how big a space you're planning,

664
00:46:56,530 --> 00:46:59,780
but you should talk to other
experienced designers, too.

665
00:46:59,780 --> 00:47:02,070
If you tell me the aesthetic you want,

666
00:47:02,070 --> 00:47:04,070
I'll do some sketches based on that.

667
00:47:04,070 --> 00:47:05,870
You can see them and decide.

668
00:47:05,870 --> 00:47:09,630
You can get a quote and decide, too.

669
00:47:09,630 --> 00:47:12,460
Why would you say that?

670
00:47:12,460 --> 00:47:15,940
- Pardon?
- It caught my attention. That's enough.

671
00:47:17,180 --> 00:47:19,240
I'd like to hire you.

672
00:47:20,160 --> 00:47:22,490
Me?

673
00:47:22,490 --> 00:47:25,670
I got a good feeling
after looking at your portfolio.

674
00:47:26,780 --> 00:47:29,980
I have an appointment today.

675
00:47:29,980 --> 00:47:32,210
I'd like to discuss details in person.

676
00:47:32,210 --> 00:47:33,870
When are you free?

677
00:47:33,870 --> 00:47:36,940
I'm free anytime.

678
00:47:36,940 --> 00:47:38,980
What about the cafe?

679
00:47:38,980 --> 00:47:42,360
I was hired as a manager
with a situation like this in mind.

680
00:47:42,360 --> 00:47:46,090
My school club's sunbae invested in this cafe.

681
00:47:46,090 --> 00:47:48,010
I thought it was a cool place.

682
00:47:48,010 --> 00:47:51,030
It was because it had cool people.

683
00:47:53,100 --> 00:47:55,060
My phone number is on the business card.

684
00:47:55,060 --> 00:47:57,730
Send me your phone number, Eun Oh.

685
00:47:57,730 --> 00:48:00,050
Okay, I will.

686
00:48:00,050 --> 00:48:02,980
See you soon, then.

687
00:48:02,980 --> 00:48:04,550
Okay.

688
00:48:09,900 --> 00:48:11,390
Daebak! Daebak!

689
00:48:11,390 --> 00:48:15,080
It's true that you get blessed if you do good.

690
00:48:15,080 --> 00:48:16,650
I don't know for sure yet.

691
00:48:16,650 --> 00:48:19,220
She might've remembered me

692
00:48:19,220 --> 00:48:22,050
helping her and hired me on impulse.

693
00:48:22,860 --> 00:48:25,010
But I hope you hear from her.

694
00:48:25,010 --> 00:48:28,320
Me, too. It'd be nice to focus on something.

695
00:48:28,320 --> 00:48:32,000
I didn't hear back from the apartment
that requested a quote, either.

696
00:49:39,970 --> 00:49:43,010
It's an alarm from hell.

697
00:49:43,010 --> 00:49:46,500
 Seongil Textile canceled the job offer to Dad. 

698
00:49:48,040 --> 00:49:50,170
 But without being able to tell us, 

699
00:49:50,170 --> 00:49:52,950
 Dad goes out looking for a job every day. 

700
00:49:58,800 --> 00:50:00,460
Wake up.

701
00:50:00,460 --> 00:50:02,560
I can't do this right now.

702
00:50:02,560 --> 00:50:05,290
They can't find out that I got fired.

703
00:50:38,760 --> 00:50:41,190
I'll catch him as soon as I see him.

704
00:50:41,190 --> 00:50:43,220
Don't worry, and go in.

705
00:50:44,580 --> 00:50:46,070
Okay.

706
00:50:46,070 --> 00:50:47,890
Thank you.

707
00:51:41,070 --> 00:51:43,150
Long time no see, Yeong Ra.

708
00:51:43,150 --> 00:51:45,460
You understand how I feel now, right?

709
00:51:56,030 --> 00:51:58,330
Yeong Ra. Yeong Ra.

710
00:51:58,330 --> 00:51:59,990
Yeong Ra.

711
00:52:01,540 --> 00:52:03,800
What's wrong, Yeong Ra?

712
00:52:03,800 --> 00:52:07,510
I thought I expressed my true feelings enough.

713
00:52:07,510 --> 00:52:09,580
I gave you this flower
at your graduation show, too.

714
00:52:09,580 --> 00:52:11,220
Don't you remember?

715
00:52:11,220 --> 00:52:13,900
Mom... Mom... gosh...

716
00:52:15,800 --> 00:52:18,100
- I'm not a scary person.
- Don't hurt me.

717
00:52:18,100 --> 00:52:20,460
- Yeong Ra.
- Don't hurt me.

718
00:52:20,460 --> 00:52:22,700
- Yeong Ra.
- What's wrong?

719
00:52:23,750 --> 00:52:25,330
Who are you?

720
00:52:31,450 --> 00:52:33,140
Ms. Park.

721
00:52:33,140 --> 00:52:34,580
Who was that?

722
00:52:34,580 --> 00:52:36,120
Should I call the police?

723
00:52:36,120 --> 00:52:38,930
 You can't get involved in any rumors. 

724
00:52:38,930 --> 00:52:41,260
No, don't.

725
00:52:42,300 --> 00:52:44,920
I-I think he's a fan.

726
00:52:44,920 --> 00:52:47,340
I got scared because he showed up out of the blue.

727
00:52:47,340 --> 00:52:50,780
Someone who shows up without
notice like that is a stalker.

728
00:52:50,780 --> 00:52:53,330
No, it's not like that.

729
00:52:54,760 --> 00:52:56,780
It's okay, Jeong Hui.

730
00:53:06,130 --> 00:53:07,960
I'm okay.

731
00:53:25,190 --> 00:53:27,740
 So, how much longer will you think about it? 

732
00:53:28,870 --> 00:53:30,880
 What do you want? 

733
00:53:31,810 --> 00:53:33,870
 What are you going to do? 

734
00:53:45,360 --> 00:53:46,990
 This is Luce Construction. 

735
00:53:46,990 --> 00:53:49,050
 Your resume has been approved. 

736
00:53:49,050 --> 00:53:52,340
 I'll let you know the interview date next week. 

737
00:53:56,840 --> 00:53:58,890
Good going.

738
00:53:59,910 --> 00:54:03,320
I thought you quit tennis three years ago.

739
00:54:03,320 --> 00:54:04,650
What are you doing here?

740
00:54:04,650 --> 00:54:05,790
How did you know I was here?

741
00:54:05,790 --> 00:54:08,140
I tracked your location. Are you happy?

742
00:54:08,140 --> 00:54:09,930
What's with you?

743
00:54:21,710 --> 00:54:24,430
- Eun Oh, you know, Ji Hyeok-
- Hey.

744
00:54:24,430 --> 00:54:26,090
That's a forbidden name.

745
00:54:26,090 --> 00:54:28,580
He doesn't come here

746
00:54:28,580 --> 00:54:32,050
and Seong Jae can't
contact him, either. Isn't that weird?

747
00:54:32,050 --> 00:54:34,960
It's weird. Very weird.

748
00:54:34,960 --> 00:54:36,850
But I need to live, too.

749
00:54:36,850 --> 00:54:38,710
I don't want to think about it.

750
00:54:39,640 --> 00:54:43,510
Okay. Lee Ji Hyeok is a forbidden name.

751
00:54:45,690 --> 00:54:47,520
You ignored my calls and texts.

752
00:54:47,520 --> 00:54:50,090
You even refuse to talk to me in person.

753
00:54:50,090 --> 00:54:51,990
Am I even your friend?

754
00:54:51,990 --> 00:54:54,350
I texted you saying I wanted to be alone.

755
00:54:54,350 --> 00:54:57,300
You had to follow me here
instead of leaving me alone?

756
00:54:57,300 --> 00:55:02,400
I searched your pool, the Han River path,
and the freediving center,

757
00:55:02,400 --> 00:55:04,890
and I came here just in case.

758
00:55:06,280 --> 00:55:09,690
Why? Is something going on? What is it?

759
00:55:09,690 --> 00:55:13,220
You know nothing ever happens to me.

760
00:55:13,220 --> 00:55:15,540
I looked for you to give you this.

761
00:55:16,490 --> 00:55:18,100
What's this?

762
00:55:18,100 --> 00:55:20,800
It's an apartment for our company's guests.

763
00:55:20,800 --> 00:55:25,240
You must've been killing time here
and there, saying you're going to work.

764
00:55:25,240 --> 00:55:27,170
Hang out there.

765
00:55:32,690 --> 00:55:37,380
You're being so considerate
when you don't know the situation.

766
00:55:37,380 --> 00:55:39,650
You...

767
00:55:39,650 --> 00:55:41,680
Don't be doing this at a place like this.

768
00:55:41,680 --> 00:55:43,330
It's pathetic.

769
00:55:43,330 --> 00:55:45,080
What's pathetic?

770
00:55:45,080 --> 00:55:48,040
Playing sports is perfect when you need to think.

771
00:55:48,040 --> 00:55:50,280
Look for a job at the apartment tomorrow.

772
00:55:50,280 --> 00:55:53,280
You haven't landed a job yet, right?

773
00:55:53,280 --> 00:55:54,860
Job?

774
00:55:54,860 --> 00:55:59,120
Doesn't your field have positions
for experienced people?

775
00:56:01,860 --> 00:56:04,390
It's not about a job. I'm thinking
about something else.

776
00:56:04,390 --> 00:56:08,180
What is it? Is something going on at home?

777
00:56:09,200 --> 00:56:14,350
I was wondering what it'd be like
to marry Jeong Bo Ah.

778
00:56:14,350 --> 00:56:16,040
Jeong Bo Ah?

779
00:56:18,330 --> 00:56:21,130
Jeong Bo Ah from Haneul Construction?

780
00:56:21,130 --> 00:56:22,900
Yes.

781
00:56:22,900 --> 00:56:27,870
She proposed to me, so I'm
considering it very seriously.

782
00:56:27,870 --> 00:56:29,660
She wants to marry you?

783
00:56:29,660 --> 00:56:32,240
She suggested that you marry her?

784
00:56:32,240 --> 00:56:33,290
Yes.

785
00:56:33,290 --> 00:56:34,700
Why?

786
00:56:35,700 --> 00:56:38,140
Because she wants to marry me?

787
00:56:38,140 --> 00:56:39,660
She does?

788
00:56:39,660 --> 00:56:41,140
Yes.

789
00:56:46,550 --> 00:56:50,070
I don't care if she's crazy or what,

790
00:56:51,070 --> 00:56:53,740
but you don't seem to be joking.

791
00:56:53,740 --> 00:56:56,910
Why should you consider that right now?

792
00:56:56,910 --> 00:56:59,020
Shouldn't I consider it?

793
00:56:59,020 --> 00:57:02,010
You and Jeong Bo Ah have nothing going on.

794
00:57:03,000 --> 00:57:06,100
Why are you so sure? Whether there's
something going on or not.

795
00:57:06,100 --> 00:57:08,620
I know. You don't love her.

796
00:57:08,620 --> 00:57:11,420
She doesn't love you, either. Am I wrong?

797
00:57:11,420 --> 00:57:14,170
Oh, love?

798
00:57:15,570 --> 00:57:17,080
No, there's no love.

799
00:57:17,080 --> 00:57:18,660
I know.

800
00:57:18,660 --> 00:57:20,880
What kind of situation is this?

801
00:57:20,880 --> 00:57:23,490
Why would she say something so ridiculous

802
00:57:23,490 --> 00:57:27,980
and why would you even consider it?

803
00:57:27,980 --> 00:57:29,600
What is this, a sitcom?

804
00:57:29,600 --> 00:57:33,960
Lee Ji Hyeok, what's wrong with you? Wake up.

805
00:57:37,120 --> 00:57:39,950
Why is love necessary, Seong Jae?

806
00:57:39,950 --> 00:57:42,840
- What?
- Why is love necessary in marriage?

807
00:57:42,840 --> 00:57:46,550
Do you have to marry someone you love?
Marriage isn't the conclusion of love.

808
00:57:46,550 --> 00:57:48,140
What are you talking about?

809
00:57:48,140 --> 00:57:49,980
Why would you want a loveless marriage? What for?

810
00:57:49,980 --> 00:57:54,050
I'm asking why love is necessary in marriage.

811
00:57:54,050 --> 00:57:56,070
Okay.

812
00:57:56,070 --> 00:57:59,900
Why do you want to marry someone you don't love?

813
00:58:01,840 --> 00:58:05,300
I don't love her, but I need to get married.

814
00:58:05,300 --> 00:58:08,700
So, why do you want a marriage like that?
Why not just live alone?

815
00:58:08,700 --> 00:58:11,660
Just be alone. I thought you were anti-marriage.

816
00:58:13,810 --> 00:58:16,750
- A marriage like that?
- Yes, a marriage like that.

817
00:58:16,750 --> 00:58:19,340
You think I don't know why she wants to marry you

818
00:58:19,340 --> 00:58:22,950
and why you want to marry her?

819
00:58:24,400 --> 00:58:26,900
- No, you don't.
- Yes, I do.

820
00:58:26,900 --> 00:58:31,200
No matter how much you try,
you can't fully understand me. I know that.

821
00:58:31,200 --> 00:58:33,140
But this is funny.

822
00:58:33,140 --> 00:58:35,320
I didn't think you'd oppose it so passionately.

823
00:58:35,320 --> 00:58:37,780
Because I'm your friend.

824
00:58:37,780 --> 00:58:40,730
I'm opposing it because I'm your friend.

825
00:58:40,730 --> 00:58:42,370
Is that so?

826
00:58:42,370 --> 00:58:43,940
Ji Hyeok,

827
00:58:45,440 --> 00:58:47,770
this isn't right.

828
00:58:50,190 --> 00:58:52,760
But listening to you,

829
00:58:53,950 --> 00:58:56,050
I think I can do this.

830
00:58:56,050 --> 00:58:59,080
Yes. I can do it.

831
00:58:59,080 --> 00:59:01,420
- What?
- This is why I didn't tell you.

832
00:59:01,420 --> 00:59:03,790
This is why I couldn't tell you.

833
00:59:03,790 --> 00:59:06,120
Because it's not something we can discuss.

834
00:59:06,120 --> 00:59:10,470
Because you'd never understand it.

835
00:59:11,600 --> 00:59:13,150
Lee Ji Hyeok,

836
00:59:14,330 --> 00:59:16,870
is this the extent of our friendship?

837
00:59:18,840 --> 00:59:22,050
There's something you can't talk about.

838
00:59:22,050 --> 00:59:23,600
There was...

839
00:59:24,600 --> 00:59:26,430
between us, too.

840
00:59:26,430 --> 00:59:28,270
What do you mean?

841
00:59:31,890 --> 00:59:33,250
I'm leaving.

842
01:00:03,440 --> 01:00:04,940
You came.

843
01:00:04,940 --> 01:00:06,520
Hey.

844
01:00:07,600 --> 01:00:10,500
Have a seat. You need to sit...

845
01:00:11,570 --> 01:00:13,860
to discuss our marriage.

846
01:00:23,290 --> 01:00:26,920
You've decided, Ji Hyeok.

847
01:00:28,960 --> 01:00:32,320
People used to marry three days
after the first blind date.

848
01:00:33,880 --> 01:00:35,710
Thank you.

849
01:00:37,500 --> 01:00:39,560
I feel reassured.

850
01:00:39,560 --> 01:00:43,440
My future won't be so unclear anymore.

851
01:00:43,440 --> 01:00:45,590
I feel the same.

852
01:00:45,590 --> 01:00:48,500
We both get something out of this marriage.

853
01:00:48,500 --> 01:00:51,780
Let's have a win-win relationship.

854
01:00:53,720 --> 01:00:58,820
Do you need a contract for a situation like this?

855
01:00:58,820 --> 01:01:00,710
That sounds awful.

856
01:01:00,710 --> 01:01:04,480
We're actually getting married.
It's not a contract marriage.

857
01:01:05,610 --> 01:01:08,740
You must have some reservations toward me.

858
01:01:09,700 --> 01:01:15,000
It sounds like you're the one
with some reservations.

859
01:01:18,020 --> 01:01:20,580
Tell me.

860
01:01:20,580 --> 01:01:24,850
My father and I want you to join our company.

861
01:01:24,850 --> 01:01:26,780
That's the biggest thing.

862
01:01:27,600 --> 01:01:29,020
If so,

863
01:01:30,780 --> 01:01:33,020
I'll tell you my terms.

864
01:01:49,040 --> 01:01:50,990
Are you nervous?

865
01:01:54,760 --> 01:01:57,950
I didn't think I'd meet him immediately like this.

866
01:02:17,320 --> 01:02:19,780
Welcome. CEO Jeong is waiting.

867
01:02:19,780 --> 01:02:21,640
I'm Lee Ji Hyeok.

868
01:02:21,640 --> 01:02:23,590
He's the CEO's chief secretary.

869
01:02:23,590 --> 01:02:26,820
Chief Cha Mun Seok and Mr. Kim.

870
01:02:27,840 --> 01:02:30,070
You have a car key in your pocket, right?

871
01:02:30,070 --> 01:02:34,950
- Yes.
- Give it to him because it makes noises.

872
01:02:34,950 --> 01:02:36,560
Okay.

873
01:02:37,960 --> 01:02:39,620
Come this way.

874
01:02:42,060 --> 01:02:44,800
Nice to meet you. I'm Lee Ji Hyeok.

875
01:02:45,650 --> 01:02:47,360
I'm Jeong Ho Yeong.

876
01:02:47,360 --> 01:02:49,250
Bo Ah's father.

877
01:02:49,250 --> 01:02:50,800
Please talk down to me.

878
01:02:50,800 --> 01:02:53,960
We should finish our handshake first.

879
01:02:55,810 --> 01:02:57,850
Have a seat.

880
01:03:01,810 --> 01:03:04,260
No need to feel uncomfortable or awkward

881
01:03:04,260 --> 01:03:06,990
right now or going forward.

882
01:03:06,990 --> 01:03:10,780
To be honest, we are not dating.

883
01:03:10,780 --> 01:03:12,400
I know.

884
01:03:12,400 --> 01:03:15,870
I know why you're getting married.

885
01:03:15,870 --> 01:03:18,600
But I like you.

886
01:03:18,600 --> 01:03:22,250
You're perfect for Bo Ah right now.

887
01:03:24,290 --> 01:03:26,600
I hope you understand what he said.

888
01:03:26,600 --> 01:03:31,530
He means everyone knows about me,
and no one on my level wants me.

889
01:03:31,530 --> 01:03:33,980
I know that much.

890
01:03:34,880 --> 01:03:38,400
Is love the priority in marriage?

891
01:03:38,400 --> 01:03:40,110
No.

892
01:03:40,110 --> 01:03:43,410
I saw my wife three times before the wedding,

893
01:03:43,410 --> 01:03:46,590
but we've been doing fine.

894
01:03:46,590 --> 01:03:48,010
Yes.

895
01:03:49,380 --> 01:03:55,450
Bo Ah will suggest a few dates
for the wedding later,

896
01:03:55,450 --> 01:03:58,090
but I'd like you to hurry.

897
01:03:59,090 --> 01:04:01,300
How about in two weeks?

898
01:04:20,960 --> 01:04:23,600
Mr. Kim brought it here.

899
01:04:26,110 --> 01:04:28,450
I'll drive with my father.

900
01:04:28,450 --> 01:04:29,950
Get in.

901
01:04:29,950 --> 01:04:31,340
Okay.

902
01:04:42,010 --> 01:04:44,330
Call me when you get your parents' approval.

903
01:04:44,330 --> 01:04:47,810
We'll proceed in the order, then.

904
01:04:47,810 --> 01:04:50,440
Okay. I'll be in touch.

